# Dropday Laravel Package

## What this is

`dropday-io/laravel` is the **official Laravel integration package** for the [Dropday](https://dropday.io) API; an order automation / dropshipping automation service. It is published under the GitHub org `dropday-io`.

## Namespace

```
Dropday\Dropday\
```

## Package structure

```
src/
  Dropday.php                  # Main HTTP client
  DropdayServiceProvider.php   # Registers singleton + publishes config
  Facades/Dropday.php          # Facade with @method docblocks
  Exceptions/DropdayException.php
config/dropday.php
```

## API conventions

- Every request requires `api-key` and `account-id` headers.
- Base URL: `https://dropday.io/api/v1` (overridable via `DROPDAY_BASE_URL`).
- HTTP 422 → throw `DropdayException`. All other errors → `$response->throw()`.
- Duplicate orders: Dropday returns HTTP 200 with `"Order already exists"` — not an error. Callers must check the `message` key if they care about duplicates.
- Pass `"test" => true` in order payloads during development to skip real supplier routing.
